00:00:33.080 --> 00:00:37.080
So, Mr. Hippelhop assigned a project to market an environmentally safe product?

00:00:37.080 --> 00:00:39.080
I thought it sounded manageable.

00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:42.080
But I haven't managed to come up with anything I like.

00:00:42.080 --> 00:00:45.080
So far, I've rejected wash-and-wear rollerblades.

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:47.080
Chusagi.

00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:49.080
Edible newspapers.

00:00:49.080 --> 00:00:52.740
Too pulpy.

00:00:52.740 --> 00:00:55.740
What about a solar-powered tanning booth?

00:00:55.740 --> 00:00:56.740
Let's see.

00:00:56.740 --> 00:00:58.740
Solar-powered tanning booth.

00:00:58.740 --> 00:01:00.740
Solar-powered tanning booth.

00:01:00.740 --> 00:01:04.240
Stop me when it sounds redundant or absolutely stupid.

00:01:04.240 --> 00:01:06.240
Well, that's my hottest idea so far.

00:01:06.240 --> 00:01:09.240
Maybe inventing isn't as easy as it looks.

00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:12.240
Too bad no one's ever come up with an invention that invents things.

00:01:12.240 --> 00:01:14.240
Hey, now that's an idea!

00:01:14.240 --> 00:02:15.890
Whatcha makin'?

00:02:15.890 --> 00:02:18.890
I need just some Hell Snacks, but I'd use it some odds and ends.

00:02:18.890 --> 00:02:20.890
Odds and ends. Too many odds and ends.

00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:22.890
That's a problem, right?

00:02:22.890 --> 00:02:24.890
Not a huge problem. Why?

00:02:24.890 --> 00:02:27.890
I had to come up with an environmentally safe product for school.

00:02:27.890 --> 00:02:30.890
I'm trying to think of a new product that solves an old problem,

00:02:30.890 --> 00:02:32.890
