00:02:38.890 --> 00:02:40.890
A solar-powered tanning booth.

00:02:40.890 --> 00:02:42.890
Wouldn't that be a little redundant?

00:02:42.890 --> 00:02:44.890
That's why it stinks, Mom.

00:02:44.890 --> 00:02:47.890
Here, taste this and tell me how you like it.

00:02:47.890 --> 00:02:48.890
What's in it?

00:02:48.890 --> 00:02:49.890
Just good stuff.

00:02:49.890 --> 00:02:57.880
Hmm, I can't believe it. These are great.

00:02:57.880 --> 00:03:02.540
Really? Not bad, is it?

00:03:02.540 --> 00:03:04.540
I need something, though.

00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:06.540
Coconut!

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:07.540
That's it.

00:03:07.540 --> 00:03:09.540
Oh, but they're already setting.

00:03:09.540 --> 00:03:11.540
Oh, I guess it's a little light to mix this in.

00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:12.540
Well, put it on top.

00:03:12.540 --> 00:03:14.540
No, here, even better.

00:03:14.540 --> 00:03:15.540
Roll in a ball.

00:03:15.540 --> 00:03:17.540
And then roll it in the coconut.

00:03:17.540 --> 00:03:23.130
Ah, that is really good.

00:03:23.130 --> 00:03:25.130
Mm-hmm.

00:03:26.130 --> 00:03:28.130
I'm sick.

00:03:28.130 --> 00:03:30.130
What's wrong, Ferguson?

00:03:30.130 --> 00:03:31.130
I'm sick.

00:03:31.130 --> 00:03:33.130
Is it a coal, flu?

00:03:33.130 --> 00:03:35.130
I'm sick.

00:03:35.130 --> 00:03:37.130
Come here, sweetheart.

00:03:37.130 --> 00:03:39.130
Oh, you do feel a little warm.

00:03:39.130 --> 00:03:42.130
Let's have a look at your throat.

00:03:42.130 --> 00:03:46.130
Oh, I guess we'll be going to see Dr. Festersfield.

00:03:46.130 --> 00:03:48.130
I'm sick.

00:03:48.130 --> 00:03:50.130
You're taking it so well, too.

00:03:50.130 --> 00:03:52.130
All right, all right, this is pathetic.

00:03:52.130 --> 00:03:55.130
You want some tea with honey and lemon?

00:03:55.130 --> 00:03:59.130
And some of those little cookies that look like elves.

00:03:59.130 --> 00:04:01.130
I'll see if there are any left.

00:04:01.130 --> 00:04:04.130
Okay, we've gotten an appointment.

00:04:04.130 --> 00:04:06.130
You know, sweetie, you're just like your dad.

00:04:06.130 --> 00:04:09.130
This is the third bad sore throat you've had this season.

00:04:09.130 --> 00:04:11.130
I know. Why me?

00:04:11.130 --> 00:04:14.130
Maybe we ought to think about getting your tonsils out.

00:04:14.130 --> 00:04:16.130
Tonsils?

00:04:16.130 --> 00:04:19.130
Me? No way.

00:04:19.130 --> 00:04:21.130
Mom, these tonsils are mine.

00:04:21.130 --> 00:04:23.130
Well, maybe you feel a lot better with them out.

00:04:23.130 --> 00:04:26.130
Oh, once you start down that road, there's no turning back.

00:04:26.130 --> 00:04:30.130
First the tonsils go, then the adenoids, then the appendix.

00:04:30.130 --> 00:04:32.130
Sure, they say it's a meaningless organ.

00:04:32.130 --> 00:04:34.130
You never know. I mean, next thing you know,

00:04:34.130 --> 00:04:36.130
I'll be walking around without a spleen.

00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:38.130
Oh, Ferguson, you're delirious.

00:04:38.130 --> 00:04:41.130
Then some crazy doctor will try to transplant a baboon's heart,

00:04:41.130 --> 00:04:43.130
a cat's liver, duct tape.

00:04:43.130 --> 00:04:44.130
What is he talking about?

00:04:44.130 --> 00:04:46.130
Sis, hang on to your organs.

00:04:46.130 --> 00:04:48.130
I promise.

00:04:48.130 --> 00:04:56.390
Ferguson, we're out of elf cookies, but here, try one of these.

00:04:56.390 --> 00:04:58.390
What's in those, rubber cement?

00:04:58.390 --> 00:05:00.390
That is so strange. I wonder what makes it bounce like that.

00:05:00.390 --> 00:05:02.390
Oh, it could be the guar gum.

00:05:02.390 --> 00:05:04.390
Let me try that.

00:05:04.390 --> 00:05:06.390
Mom, these are great.

00:05:06.390 --> 00:05:08.390
