But it seems to me something called Apple Jacks should...

00:13:23.100 --> 00:13:24.140
Tastes like Apple.

00:13:24.140 --> 00:13:25.260
Precisely.

00:13:25.260 --> 00:13:27.260
Are they supposed to taste like Apple?

00:13:27.260 --> 00:13:28.220
Keep eating.

00:13:28.220 --> 00:13:29.660
That isn't why we like them.

00:13:29.660 --> 00:13:30.380
Enlighten me.

00:13:32.140 --> 00:13:32.540
Uh...

00:13:33.980 --> 00:13:35.020
We just do.

00:13:35.020 --> 00:13:35.660
Yeah!

00:13:36.940 --> 00:13:39.660
Kellogg's Apple Jacks stereo is part of this complete breakfast.

00:13:39.660 --> 00:13:40.540
We won't be late.

00:13:44.380 --> 00:13:46.860
The call can be heard from near and far,

00:13:46.860 --> 00:13:48.460
and kids are answering it.

00:13:50.060 --> 00:13:52.540
It's Nickelodeon's Legends of the Hidden Temple,

00:13:52.540 --> 00:13:55.500
where kids conquer mysterious challenges of mind and body,

00:13:55.500 --> 00:13:58.140
scale great heights, and battle mighty foes.

00:13:58.140 --> 00:14:01.100
And it's the only show where kids can talk to a rock.

00:14:01.100 --> 00:14:02.940
Don't take me for granted.

00:14:05.790 --> 00:14:06.830
Heed the call.

00:14:07.550 --> 00:14:10.750
And watch every weekday at 5.3430 Central,

00:14:10.750 --> 00:14:12.030
only on Nickelodeon.

00:14:14.280 --> 00:14:15.960
Define kids in two seconds.

00:14:16.600 --> 00:14:17.480
One, two.

00:14:18.120 --> 00:14:20.040
You couldn't even if you had an hour,

00:14:20.040 --> 00:14:21.400
because we're all different.

00:14:21.400 --> 00:14:23.800
We come in different shapes, different colors.

00:14:23.800 --> 00:14:24.760
We like different things.

00:14:24.760 --> 00:14:26.120
We go to different schools.

00:14:26.120 --> 00:14:29.240
But the one thing that we all have in common is that we're kids.

00:14:29.240 --> 00:14:32.520
And just because of that, we all have Nickelodeon.

00:14:32.520 --> 00:14:33.720
Nick makes you laugh.

00:14:33.720 --> 00:14:35.000
It lets you think.

00:14:35.000 --> 00:14:37.560
It lets you know that you can make a difference.

00:14:37.560 --> 00:14:39.320
So if you're a kid, by definition,

00:14:39.320 --> 00:14:41.480
you belong here with Nickelodeon.

00:14:41.480 --> 00:14:43.080
Because Nick is kids.

00:14:45.160 --> 00:14:46.520
Hi, Lisa Vale here.

00:14:46.520 --> 00:14:47.720
I've always wanted to do this,

00:14:47.720 --> 00:14:49.320
and now that we're live, I'm gonna...

00:14:49.320 --> 00:14:51.480
Here's my impression of Rosie Perez.

00:14:51.480 --> 00:14:54.120
And now back to Clarissa on Snick, right?

00:14:55.720 --> 00:15:03.630
So, it's been business as usual here at Bouncy Ball Incorporated.

00:15:03.630 --> 00:15:05.230
We've got license to operate.

00:15:05.230 --> 00:15:06.430
Happy client.

00:15:06.430 --> 00:15:08.270
And Mom and I are getting along just fine.

00:15:08.990 --> 00:15:10.430
Really? We're fine.

00:15:11.070 --> 00:15:13.630
I mean, all business partners have their disagreements, right?

00:15:14.750 --> 00:15:15.310
Okay.

00:15:15.310 --> 00:15:17.470
So we got into our first argument over the packaging.

00:15:18.270 --> 00:15:20.510
I wanted to put bouncy balls in a see-through globe.

00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:23.950
But Mom felt they looked best in a line.

00:15:23.950 --> 00:15:25.070
More orderly.

00:15:25.070 --> 00:15:25.870
I guess it's okay.

00:15:26.830 --> 00:15:29.310
Then we failed to see eye-to-eye on the new flavor.

00:15:29.310 --> 00:15:30.510
Mom wanted carob.

00:15:30.510 --> 00:15:32.910
I wanted peanut butter, because, come on,

00:15:32.910 --> 00:15:35.310
people only eat carob when they're out of chocolate, right?

00:15:35.310 --> 00:15:38.430
So we disgusted, democratically, as equals, fair and square.

00:15:38.990 --> 00:15:40.030
This is our new flavor.

00:15:40.990 --> 00:15:41.470
Carob.

00:15:43.740 --> 00:15:45.420
Now we're on to advertising.

00:15:45.420 --> 00:15:47.500
Local cable's got great cheap rates,

00:15:47.500 --> 00:15:49.660
so we've decided to run an ad.

00:15:49.660 --> 00:15:51.980
The only problem is, which ad?

00:15:51.980 --> 00:15:52.940
Well, we talked about it.

00:15:53.500 --> 00:15:55.420
Mom likes the mellow nutritional approach.

00:15:56.140 --> 00:15:58.300
Sometimes, when life gets too hectic,

00:15:58.300 --> 00:16:00.380
it's good to get back to nature,

00:16:00.380 --> 00:16:04.140
and get some nature back into you, with bouncy balls.

00:16:05.580 --> 00:16:07.820
While I prefer a funkier approach.

00:16:07.820 --> 00:16:26.720
Write some photos and get some to your dog.

00:16:26.720 --> 00:16:39.210
Why do I have the feeling mellow is going to win out?

00:16:40.010 --> 00:16:42.170
It's not that my mom doesn't listen to my ideas.

00:16:42.170 --> 00:16:45.210
It's just that she gets so excited about her own ideas,

00:16:45.210 --> 00:16:46.330
and she's my mom.

00:16:46.330 --> 00:16:47.290
I can't compete.

00:16:47.930 --> 00:16:48.490
Hi, Sam.

00:16:50.430 --> 00:16:50.990
Hi, Sam.

00:16:57.260 --> 00:16:58.060
Hey, Clarissa.

00:17:00.440 --> 00:17:01.640
Brought you present.

00:17:01.640 --> 00:17:03.080
Your very own bath brick.

00:17:03.080 --> 00:17:03.800
Well, thanks.

00:17:04.680 --> 00:17:06.600
No one else wanted to try it, except my dad.

00:17:07.400 --> 00:17:08.040
Did you like it?

00:17:08.680 --> 00:17:10.760
Not really. He stubbed his toe on it.

00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:13.080
So how's business going?

00:17:13.080 --> 00:17:14.360
Well, we've got plenty of orders.

00:17:14.360 --> 00:17:16.200
It's just my mom.

00:17:17.000 --> 00:17:18.280
She's not pulling her weight.

00:17:18.280 --> 00:17:20.120
Oh, she's doing more than her fair share.

00:17:20.120 --> 00:17:22.040
She's doing my fair share, too.

00:17:22.040 --> 00:17:23.640
So much for equal partnership.

00:17:24.360 --> 00:17:26.040
Clarissa, oh, hi, Samuel.

00:17:26.120 --> 00:17:28.040
I just talked to the cable station about the ads,

00:17:28.040 --> 00:17:30.280
and we've decided to go to the major campaign.

00:17:30.280 --> 00:17:31.480
Isn't this exciting?

00:17:31.480 --> 00:17:31.960
Oh, yeah.

00:17:33.960 --> 00:17:36.040
See, whenever we have a decision to make,

00:17:36.040 --> 00:17:37.160
she gets her opinion.

00:17:37.160 --> 00:17:38.360
I give my opinion,

00:17:38.360 --> 00:17:40.200
and then we always end up using her opinion.

00:17:40.760 --> 00:17:43.000
So if she's bossing you around, shouldn't you just tell her?

00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:44.440
I guess I'd better.

00:17:45.240 --> 00:17:47.320
You know the tricky thing about having a family business?

00:17:48.280 --> 00:17:49.640
How do you deal with your family?

00:17:52.910 --> 00:17:54.910
Fester spoons are quack, Janet.

00:17:54.910 --> 00:17:57.230
Nobody made you get your throat examined, Marshall.

00:17:58.030 --> 00:18:01.070
Ridiculous guy my age, having his tonsils out.

00:18:01.070 --> 00:18:04.030
Well, you are just getting over another case of tonsillitis.

00:18:04.590 --> 00:18:05.710
I'm a grown-up.

00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:06.590
I can handle it.

00:18:08.990 --> 00:18:10.670
Do we have any more popsicles left?

00:18:10.670 --> 00:18:12.830
I think you ate the last of them, dear.

00:18:13.950 --> 00:18:16.030
I'll sit for the hospital, Ferguson.

00:18:16.030 --> 00:18:16.670
Almost.

00:18:16.670 --> 00:18:18.510
I've just got one thing to take care of.

00:18:20.190 --> 00:18:24.030
I, Ferguson W. Darling, being of sound mind and body,

00:18:24.030 --> 00:18:24.270
do you hear about...

00:18:24.270 --> 00:18:24.830
What is that?

00:18:25.390 --> 00:18:25.870
My will.

00:18:26.590 --> 00:18:28.590
That's for 75 pages long.

00:18:28.590 --> 00:18:29.710
Actually, 82.

00:18:29.710 --> 00:18:34.190
Yeah, well, Ferguson, you can read the rest of it to me in the car.

00:18:34.190 --> 00:18:36.190
We're supposed to check in by four o'clock.

00:18:36.190 --> 00:18:39.630
That is unless, of course, you know, go to Tijuana instead.

00:18:39.630 --> 00:18:40.110
Sounds good.

00:18:41.070 --> 00:18:42.030
Uh-huh, you guys.

00:18:42.030 --> 00:18:44.190
Chris and I will be over this evening to tuck you in.

00:18:44.750 --> 00:18:46.750
And tomorrow morning, zero hour.

00:18:48.350 --> 00:18:49.710
Oh, don't make me go, Mom.

00:18:49.710 --> 00:18:50.190
Oh.

00:18:50.190 --> 00:18:51.150
Come on, Ferguson.

00:18:52.190 --> 00:18:53.950
I'll see you both later.

00:18:53.950 --> 00:18:58.720
So should we go over next week's budget?

00:18:59.840 --> 00:19:01.120
Mom, can we talk?

00:19:02.080 --> 00:19:02.880
Sure, what is it?

00:19:03.920 --> 00:19:05.280
It's a whole partnership.

00:19:05.280 --> 00:19:07.360
It feels a little out of balance to me.

00:19:07.360 --> 00:19:08.400
How do you mean?

00:19:08.400 --> 00:19:10.640
Like, some of us are doing more than others.

00:19:10.640 --> 00:19:13.120
Oh, Chris, I don't expect you to put in the hours I do.

00:19:13.120 --> 00:19:15.520
You've got school, and that's definitely the priority.

00:19:15.520 --> 00:19:17.600
Uh-huh, but I want more input.

00:19:17.600 --> 00:19:20.000
Well, you created the whole concept of bouncy balls.

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:22.320
Don't worry, I'm having a really good time doing this.

00:19:22.320 --> 00:19:23.760
Mom, I don't think you're hearing me.

00:19:24.320 --> 00:19:25.520
Oh, hold that thought.

00:19:29.160 --> 00:19:29.640
Hello?

00:19:30.280 --> 00:19:30.920
Yes, it is.

00:19:32.280 --> 00:19:33.560
Chelsea Chippley?

00:19:33.560 --> 00:19:35.640
V, Chelsea Chippley of Health Mountain?

00:19:36.600 --> 00:19:37.800
Of course I have.

00:19:38.680 --> 00:19:40.840
Your books on wheat gluten are the best.

00:19:42.280 --> 00:19:42.840
You would?

00:19:43.960 --> 00:19:44.360
Really?

00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:47.400
Oh, gee, I guess so.

00:19:47.400 --> 00:19:48.840
Um, tomorrow at three?

00:19:49.640 --> 00:19:50.120
Okay.

00:19:51.240 --> 00:19:51.640
Bye.

00:19:53.640 --> 00:19:55.320
You'll never guess who that was.

00:19:55.960 --> 00:19:57.480
Chelsea Chippley.

00:19:57.480 --> 00:19:58.760
Who's Chelsea Chippley?

00:19:58.760 --> 00:20:00.120
Only the owner of Health Mountain.

00:20:00.920 --> 00:20:03.720
Oh, the company that makes all that yucky health junk?

00:20:03.720 --> 00:20:04.760
It's not junk.

00:20:04.760 --> 00:20:06.520
You eat their products every day.

00:20:06.520 --> 00:20:07.880
Chelsea tried our bouncy balls.

00:20:07.880 --> 00:20:10.760
She wants to buy them and sell them through Health Mountain.

00:20:10.760 --> 00:20:11.240
No way!

00:20:12.120 --> 00:20:12.600
Yes!

00:20:12.600 --> 00:20:13.800
Isn't this exciting?

00:20:13.800 --> 00:20:19.530
So there are real advantages to letting Health Mountain

00:20:19.530 --> 00:20:21.050
market bouncy balls.

00:20:21.050 --> 00:20:22.890
But bouncy balls is our product.

00:20:22.890 --> 00:20:26.090
I thought the whole idea of this was that we'd go into business together.

00:20:26.090 --> 00:20:28.970
They would be able to sell them on a national level.

00:20:29.530 --> 00:20:30.970
Well, so will we one day.

00:20:31.690 --> 00:20:32.090
Maybe.

00:20:32.810 --> 00:20:33.930
What's Health Mountain gonna do?

00:20:33.930 --> 00:20:36.010
Put a bunch of sappy poetry quotes on the label?

00:20:36.570 --> 00:20:38.890
Look, I have to insist that we hear Chelsea Chippley out.

00:20:38.890 --> 00:20:40.730
And I have to insist you hear me out.

00:20:40.730 --> 00:20:42.890
I'm half of this company and I'm not selling.

00:20:43.930 --> 00:20:44.410
We'll see.

00:20:49.280 --> 00:20:50.880
I don't like this idea.

00:20:50.880 --> 00:20:53.440
Mom seems bent on selling and I'm really opposed to it.

00:20:54.160 --> 00:20:56.880
Guess we're just gonna have to battle it out between the two of us.

00:20:56.880 --> 00:21:05.850
We'll do young one, but you are not yet a gourmet cook.

00:21:07.290 --> 00:21:09.290
It is useful to resist.

00:21:09.290 --> 00:21:12.010
Don't let yourself be destroyed like Eddie Crofton.

00:21:13.450 --> 00:21:19.450
Join me at Health Mountain and together we can end this destructive conflict over the basketball empire.

00:21:21.130 --> 00:21:24.090
No, I'll never join you at Health Mountain.

00:21:24.090 --> 00:21:28.010
I am your mother and I can make you.

00:21:28.890 --> 00:21:30.650
No, it can't be true.

00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:32.330
It's impossible.

00:21:33.370 --> 00:21:37.930
Join me and together we can rule the snap food world as mother and doctrine.

00:21:38.730 --> 00:21:40.490
Come with me.

00:21:40.490 --> 00:21:42.170
It is the only way.

00:21:50.720 --> 00:21:54.800
I've got to find some way to get through to mom before this whole thing spins out of control.

00:21:57.600 --> 00:22:00.080
Well, all's quiet on the bouncy ball front.

00:22:00.080 --> 00:22:02.160
Mom and I aren't really speaking to each other.

00:22:02.160 --> 00:22:04.320
And what with dad and Ferguson having time select to me,

00:22:04.320 --> 00:22:06.640
there isn't a lot of small talk in the Dirling household.

00:22:08.320 --> 00:22:09.520
Hey guys, how you feeling?

00:22:13.160 --> 00:22:14.680
Dad, here's your tea.

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:17.640
You're having more ice cream?

00:22:17.640 --> 00:22:18.760
Doesn't that stuff hurt your throat?

00:22:18.760 --> 00:22:20.920
I mean, you had your tonsils out like five hours ago.

00:22:23.130 --> 00:22:23.690
Bye, guys.

00:22:26.910 --> 00:22:29.230
I'm getting tired of holding up conversation around here.

00:22:30.510 --> 00:22:32.190
Oh, that'll be Chelsea Chippley.

00:22:32.190 --> 00:22:34.510
I better prepare for war and have one fair.

00:22:34.510 --> 00:22:35.710
I'm already outnumbered.

00:22:38.570 --> 00:22:41.290
Clarissa, I'd like you to meet Chelsea Chippley.

00:22:41.290 --> 00:22:42.010
Hi.

00:22:42.010 --> 00:22:45.770
So you're the whiz kid behind bouncy balls, am I?

00:22:46.410 --> 00:22:47.530
Please sit down.

00:22:47.530 --> 00:22:50.570
It's a pleasure to meet the woman on top of Health Mountain.

00:22:50.570 --> 00:22:52.410
It's such a great company.

00:22:52.490 --> 00:22:55.850
Hey, it's nice to know that people share our concerns.

00:22:56.410 --> 00:23:00.970
I'm very proud of what we stand for, health, nature, good karma,

00:23:01.850 --> 00:23:05.450
and bouncy balls will fit in beautifully with our philosophy.

00:23:05.450 --> 00:23:06.730
I think so too.

00:23:06.730 --> 00:23:07.690
Thank you, Janet.

00:23:08.650 --> 00:23:10.810
Clarissa, this is what I'm thinking.

00:23:10.810 --> 00:23:14.810
If there's one thing that Health Mountain cares about as much as health, it's kids.

00:23:15.610 --> 00:23:19.530
We plan to market bouncy balls as a kid food,

00:23:19.530 --> 00:23:22.090
good for kids, made by kids.

00:23:23.130 --> 00:23:25.530
Well, thanks, but actually my mom made them.

00:23:26.250 --> 00:23:28.170
Oh, oh, that's terrific.

00:23:28.730 --> 00:23:31.290
Well, aren't you just a marvel in the kitchen?

00:23:32.890 --> 00:23:33.930
But I can't use that.

00:23:34.890 --> 00:23:36.410
You, I can use.

00:23:36.410 --> 00:23:40.730
We need to open up the wonders of nature to a youthful audience.

00:23:41.450 --> 00:23:44.010
We'll put your face on the package.

00:23:44.010 --> 00:23:44.810
How about that?

00:23:45.450 --> 00:23:46.330
I don't know.

00:23:46.330 --> 00:23:47.610
Sounds great, Clarissa.

00:23:48.170 --> 00:23:50.650
By the way, where did you try bouncy balls?

00:23:50.650 --> 00:23:51.770
The health hideaway?

00:23:51.770 --> 00:23:59.610
Oh, no, this cute little place, license plates on the walls, Bubba's rib shack, that's it.

00:24:00.170 --> 00:24:03.690
Boy, it's kind of run down, but does that man know his ribs?

00:24:03.690 --> 00:24:04.650
Can you eat ribs?

00:24:06.650 --> 00:24:07.610
Oh, no.

00:24:07.610 --> 00:24:08.490
No, no.

00:24:08.490 --> 00:24:11.290
Oh, well, he just said that Bubba makes great ribs.

00:24:12.010 --> 00:24:15.770
Well, maybe I had just one little bite, so shoot me, right?

00:24:16.410 --> 00:24:19.290
Well, I'm just surprised in your book, My Earth, My Garden,

00:24:19.290 --> 00:24:21.850
you're such an advocate of vegetarianism.

00:24:23.290 --> 00:24:24.650
Oh, that's right.

00:24:24.650 --> 00:24:26.250
Is that something that can flip your mind?

00:24:27.370 --> 00:24:28.490
Absolutely not.

00:24:29.210 --> 00:24:32.410
Vegetarianism is very important to me.

00:24:32.410 --> 00:24:38.640
What about some bouncy balls?

00:24:38.640 --> 00:24:39.680
I just made a fresh batch.

00:24:39.680 --> 00:24:41.200
Oh, I would love one.

00:24:42.000 --> 00:24:44.730
You really do like them, don't you?

00:24:44.730 --> 00:24:45.690
Oh, I love them.

00:24:45.690 --> 00:24:46.970
They are so sweet.

00:24:46.970 --> 00:24:50.170
I mean, you would never believe that's a health food.

00:24:50.170 --> 00:24:51.450
Normally, I hate this stuff.

00:24:52.170 --> 00:24:55.530
Oh, come on, all those adzuki beans.

00:24:55.850 --> 00:24:57.050
Browse, seaweed.

00:24:58.730 --> 00:25:00.490
Then why do you run Health Mountain?

00:25:01.210 --> 00:25:04.170
Because there are enough granola heads out there to make a killing.

00:25:05.610 --> 00:25:07.450
Oh, no offense, Jen.

00:25:08.810 --> 00:25:11.290
Anyway, back to business.

00:25:11.290 --> 00:25:14.330
I am going to need your signatures on this.

00:25:14.970 --> 00:25:15.690
A contract?

00:25:16.810 --> 00:25:20.170
Basically, it says that we'll own bouncy balls and all ancillary rights,

00:25:20.170 --> 00:25:23.610
including video merchandising, foreign licensing and perpetuity,

00:25:23.610 --> 00:25:25.610
in this form and any not yet invented.

00:25:26.010 --> 00:25:30.970
And that Clarissa will be needed for consulting and advertising.

00:25:31.530 --> 00:25:33.210
And what did you have in mind for me?

00:25:34.090 --> 00:25:34.490
Nothing.

00:25:36.170 --> 00:25:38.890
Oh, now, don't take it personally with the you thing.

00:25:38.890 --> 00:25:40.730
Well, neither of us is going to be much help.

00:25:41.530 --> 00:25:42.170
Believe me.

00:25:43.450 --> 00:25:46.810
Well, this is an excellent opportunity for you, Clarissa.

00:25:47.850 --> 00:25:51.930
I knew you wouldn't stand in the way of your daughter's success.

00:25:52.810 --> 00:25:54.730
She's not standing in my way.

00:25:54.810 --> 00:25:55.690
We're partners.

00:25:55.690 --> 00:25:57.770
We make decisions together, right, Mom?

00:25:57.770 --> 00:26:00.570
Oh, please, your mom doesn't care.

00:26:00.570 --> 00:26:02.410
Well, actually, yes, I do.

00:26:02.410 --> 00:26:05.050
And we care what happens to bouncy balls even if you don't.

00:26:13.450 --> 00:26:18.200
Well, well, I guess I'm wasting my time.

00:26:19.880 --> 00:26:25.720
As far as I'm concerned, you can take your bouncy balls and bounce them.

00:26:25.720 --> 00:26:36.350
I didn't expect Chelsea Chippley to be so unhealthy.

00:26:36.350 --> 00:26:36.910
Exactly.

00:26:37.710 --> 00:26:39.390
You know, you're right.

00:26:40.190 --> 00:26:42.590
It's not much fun being left out of the process.

00:26:43.230 --> 00:26:46.110
